### Rinaldo Del Bo: A Political Career

Rinaldo Del Bo, a figure whose life spanned from 1916 to 1991, carved a significant path within [Italian politics](/Politics_of_Italy). His tenure included a notable position within the [High Authority of the](/High_Authority_of_the_European_Coal_and_Steel_Community) [European Coal and Steel Community](/European_Coal_and_Steel_Community) (ECSC). During his leadership, from October 22, 1963, to March 8, 1967, he presided over what became known as the [Del Bo Authority](/Del_Bo_Authority), a period that marked a distinct phase in the ECSC’s operational history.

